ettles the hegemonic narrative of dominant media, as well as the apparently politically neutral dimension of communication technology. In this book, the author explores how video-image technology shapes our psychic and social environments from an art historiographical perspective. We know media technology is dramatically shaping our political and epistemological landscape: this book foregrounds the emergence of performative video images as a key factor in the revaluation of culture and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt and technologyzFrancexHistory. 0aVideo artzFrancexHistory. 0aVideo artzFrancexPhilosophy. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aMedia Studies. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aThierry Kuntzel, Video Art, Performance Studies, Media Studies, France.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048550289?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048550289423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048550289/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles